# <type>(<scope>): <imperative subject, ~72 chars, no trailing period>
#
# Common types: chore, feat, fix, docs, ci, refactor, test
# Scopes: area of change (e.g. prettier, fly, scripts, deps) — optional but helps git log filters
#
# Body (optional): use for non-obvious changes — short bullets for what/why (e.g. why ignore a path).
# Separate subject and body with a blank line.
#
# Conventional Commits: https://www.conventionalcommits.org/
#
# Lines starting with # are ignored by git.
